# Learning How To Learn: What are the focused and diffuse modes of thinking?

## Focused mode

When you concentrate intently on something you're trying to learn or to understand.

Analogous to a game of pinball with the bumpers very close to each other: A thought pattern corresponds to a path travelled by the ball as it bounces between the bumpers. The density of the bumpers makes it easy to travel a familiar path, but harder to create a new path as there are so many bumpers in the way.

## Diffuse mode

A more relaxed state of thinking correlating to neural resting states. So 'big picture thinking' is easier.

Analagous to a game of pinball where the bumpers are very far apart, so the ball travels further between each bumper collision and it is easier for new paths (ideas) to be formed between disassociated areas.

